h1 Create new campaign
form#new_campaign_form
  .level-one
    .form-group
      label Title
      input.form-control type="text"
    .form-group
      label Description
      textarea.form-control placeholder=("Enter as much information here as possible to describe your campaign and what you are trying to achieve. Others will see this description unless the campaign is accessible to collaborators only.") rows="6" type="text"
      small.form-text
        | Surround content with an asterisk on each side to make it
        i  italic
        |  Surround content with two asterisks on each side to make it
        b  bold
    .actions.pull-right
      input#one-next.btn.btn-primary type="button" value="Next"
  .level-two.mt-5
    .form-group
      label This campaign will be accessible to:
    .campaign-visibility
      .form-group
        label.radio-inline
          input.mr-2 checked="" name="optradio" type="radio"
          | Everyone
        p This campaign will be visible to other PolicyMogul users and may be indexed by search engines. Specific documents, collaborators and other information you choose can be made available to campaign collaborators only.
      .form-group
        label.radio-inline
          input.mr-2 checked="" name="optradio" type="radio"
          | Parliamentarians and collaborators only
        p PolicyMogul maintains a list of MPs and peers, and allows them and their staff to view campaigns related to their interests. Specific documents, collaborators and other information you choose can be made available to campaign collaborators only.
      .form-group
        label.radio-inline
          input.mr-2 checked="" name="optradio" type="radio"
          | Collaborators only
        p This campaign will not be displayed to others; you will need to invite specific people in order to collaborate with them.
    .actions.pull-right
      input#two-prev.btn.btn-primary.mr-2 type="button" value="Previous"
      input#two-next.btn.btn-primary type="button" value="Next"
